 national boundaries. It utilizes the latest available demographic, social, and economic data through state-of-the-art geographical information systems and new cartography techniques. Through these new visualizations, this highly illustrated book offers fresh perspectives on a range of topics, including social values, culture, education, employment, environmental footprints, health and well-being, and social inequalities and cohesion. It is a bold rethinking of Europe as we know it and will be of interest to anyone who wants to understand the continent in its truest form.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aHuman geographyvMapszEurope. 0aHuman geographyzEuropevMaps. 0aHuman geographyzEurope. 0aPopulation geographyvMapszEurope. 0aPopulation geographyzEuropevMaps. 0aPopulation geographyzEurope. 7aREFERENCE / Atlases, Gazetteers & Maps (see also Travel / Maps & Road Atlases).2bisacsh1 aDorling, Danny, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHennig, Benjamin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2014z9783111196343oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978144731353340uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447313557?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447313557423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447313557/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPb2014